  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau R. F. and A. L <lb/>Head Qus. 9th Sub Dist. Va 
     <name type="recipient">Thomas P. Jackson</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-09-11">September 11, 1867</date>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Respectfully returned to Mr. Thos. P. Jackson, agent. </salute>
    </opener>

    <p>The only way in which <hi rend="underline">Collins</hi> can obtain a legal separation from his wife is to sue
     for a divorce. To erase the name from the Register, while, it could not be authorized, would
     not alter the fact of his being legally married to her. The registrat ion is only an
      <hi rend="underline">evidence</hi> of marriage. He would be legally married, whether registered or not. </p>

    <closer>
     <salute/>
     <signed>John A McDonnell, Capt A. S. A. C. </signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
